Hamilton, who was visibly emotional after speaking to Rosberg about the incident, claimed: ‘I was gobsmacked when I was in the meeting.

‘He (Nico) basically said he did it on purpose. He said he could have avoided it. He said he did it to prove a point. He said it was all my fault.’

That last comment referred to the animosity that has been building up between the two men for months. Rosberg was angry that Hamilton cut across him in Bahrain; Hamilton felt Rosberg deliberately scuppered his qualifying lap in Monaco; and, perhaps most importantly, Rosberg was still fuming that Hamilton did not follow a team order at the last race in Hungary. 

