Hamilton added: ‘When you’re out there you have to trust people not to do things deliberately, but after that meeting I don’t really know how to approach the next race.

‘All I know is I’ve got to push. The support has been great - so many British flags and tops, and I’m gutted I wasn’t able to get a result for them this weekend.’

Rosberg was booed by Hamilton’s supporters on the podium after coming second to Red Bull’s Daniel Ricciardo. The German now leads the championship by 29 points with seven races remaining. 

