Rosberg’s management did not respond to Hamilton’s claims directly, saying he prefers to ‘discuss things internally’. However, Rosberg publicly mainatained it was ‘a racing incident’ rather than a deliberate act of malice.

However, his team bosses did not agree on Sunday. Niki Lauda, the Mercedes chairman, said: ‘It is unacceptable that in the second lap Nico hit Lewis, completely unacceptable.

‘If these things happen at the end of the race, when they are fighting for the win then OK, but in the second lap to hand the victory to Red Bull is madness.’

